  "text": "Moreover, there is ample evidence that analogical reasoning performance can be directly trained, including the studies my colleagues and I have conducted with children and adults. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Others have documented similar effects for interventions involving analogical reasoning. [CITATION_4] The question remains whether similar training outcomes to those documented for analogies would be expected for the other forms of relational reasoning, anomaly, antithesis, and antinomy.",
